cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about dialogue management in task-oriented dialogue systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel policy model based on a recurrent cell, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing models and the need for robustness, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
